---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Site/Navigation';
import Footer from '../components/Site/Footer';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms and Conditions | Inspectr"
  description="Terms and Conditions for Inspectr, including service usage terms for local deployments and Inspectr Expose remote ingress."
  keywords="Inspectr terms, terms and conditions, inspectr expose terms, legal"
  ogTitle="Terms and Conditions | Inspectr"
  ogDescription="Read the Terms and Conditions for using Inspectr local deployments and Inspectr Expose remote ingress."
  canonical="https://inspectr.dev/terms/"
>
  <Navigation client:load />

  <main class="bg-brand-dark text-white">
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14 sm:py-18">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: April 21, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-200 leading-7">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            By accessing or using Inspectr, you agree to these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree,
            you must not use Inspectr services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">2. Service Description and Current Service Model</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr provides API, webhook, and MCP traffic inspection tooling across two distinct offerings:
            (a) the local Inspectr software you install and operate in your own environment ("Inspectr
            Software"), and (b) the Inspectr ingress/expose offering used to forward public traffic to your
            local environment ("Inspectr Service").
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr services are operated from Belgium, with DNS managed by Cloudflare and hosting
            provided by Delta.blue infrastructure in Europe.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr Software is open-source and available through GitHub. Inspectr Service is currently
            offered with a simple commercial plan. Additional or updated commercial terms may be published
            and will apply only from their effective date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">3. Service Modes: Local and Expose</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            For Inspectr Software (local installation), request and response data processing and storage
            occur in your own environment under your control. For Inspectr Service (ingress/expose), ingress
            infrastructure is used only to accept and forward encrypted traffic to your local Inspectr
            instance.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr Service (ingress/expose) is forwarding-only and does not store request details or
            sensitive information from proxied traffic on the ingress side, including request bodies, query
            parameters, headers, and response payload content.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Any traffic handling required to route a live connection is transient and non-persistent. This
            forwarding-only, non-storage commitment is a material term of these Terms and Conditions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You agree not to use Inspectr to violate applicable law, interfere with service operations,
            transmit malicious payloads, or process data without an appropriate legal basis.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You must not use Inspectr Service to attempt unauthorized access, distribute malware, perform
            denial-of-service activity, or relay unlawful content.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">5. User Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You are responsible for configuration choices, security controls in your own environment, and
            ensuring that your use of Inspectr is compliant with data protection and sector-specific
            obligations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">6. No Storage Commitment for Ingress Payload Data</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr Service ingress/expose does not persist request/response payload content from proxied
            traffic. This includes request bodies, response bodies, headers, query parameters, and similar
            sensitive payload details.
          </p>
          <!--<p class="mt-2">-->
          <!--  This commitment does not prevent transient technical handling that is strictly necessary to-->
          <!--  forward a live request.-->
          <!--</p>-->
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr branding, hosted service features, and related materials remain the intellectual
            property of Inspectr and its licensors. Open-source components are governed by their respective
            licenses.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">8. Availability and Service Changes</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We may change, limit, or discontinue parts of Inspectr Service at any time, including free
            access features, to maintain security, stability, or legal compliance.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We do not provide a guaranteed uptime commitment unless a separate written agreement explicitly
            states otherwise.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Inspectr services are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind,
            express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
            non-infringement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Inspectr is not liable for indirect, incidental,
            special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for loss of profits, revenue, data, or use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">11. Suspension and Termination</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We may suspend or terminate access where required to protect service integrity, address abuse,
            or comply with legal obligations. You may stop using Inspectr at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">12. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Our data handling commitments and role allocation are described in the Privacy Policy. In case of
            conflict between these Terms and the Privacy Policy for data-handling statements, the Privacy
            Policy governs.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">13. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            These Terms are governed by the laws of Belgium, excluding conflict of laws rules. Disputes
            are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the competent courts in Brussels, Belgium.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">14. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We may update these Terms from time to time. Material updates are effective when posted on this
            page with a revised "Last updated" date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">15. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Questions about these Terms can be sent to
            <a class="text-brand-primary hover:underline ml-1" href="mailto:legal@inspectr.dev">
              legal@inspectr.dev
            </a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
